<div class="article-headline" id="Headline">LEMON HERB ROASTED CHICKEN</div>



<div class="article-in-image" id="image1"><img src="images/page059.article004.image1.jpg" class="article-in-image" alt=""/></div>
<div id="separatorLine"> <div class="invisible">empty</div> </div>

<div class="articleImageCredit" id="ImageCredit">PHOTOGRAPHY BY KAMIN WILLIAMS</div>
<div class="article-body" id="Body"><p class="no-indent">Makes 4 to 6 servings </p><br/><p class="no-indent">1 (4½ to 5-pound) whole chicken* </p><p class="no-indent">¾ cup loosely packed cilantro leaves </p><p class="no-indent">½ cup loosely packed parsley leaves </p><p class="no-indent">2 teaspoons minced garlic </p><p class="no-indent">1 teaspoon lemon zest </p><p class="no-indent">½ teaspoon salt </p><p class="no-indent">½ teaspoon ground black pepper </p><p class="no-indent">4 tablespoons olive oil, divided </p><p class="no-indent">1 (24-ounce) bag gourmet potato blend </p><br/><p class="no-indent">1. Preheat oven to 350°. Line a roasting pan with aluminum foil. Place rack over foil. </p><br/><p class="no-indent">2. Remove and discard giblets from chicken. Using paper towels, pat chicken dry. Place chicken, breast side up on prepared rack. </p><br/><p class="no-indent">3. In the work bowl of a food processor, combine cilantro, next 5 ingredients and 3 tablespoons oil. Process until finely chopped. </p><br/><p class="no-indent">4. Loosen skin from chicken breast, and rub two-thirds of herb mixture under skin. Replace skin over breast, and rub remaining herb mixture over chicken. Using kitchen twine, tie chicken legs together, and tuck wing tips under chicken. </p><br/><p class="no-indent">5. In a large bowl, combine potatoes and remaining 1 tablespoon olive oil, tossing to coat. Place potatoes around chicken in pan. </p><br/><p class="no-indent">6. Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour. Cover loosely with aluminum foil, and bake for 30 to 45 minutes longer, or until a thermometer inserted in thickest portion registers 165˚. Let stand for 10 minutes before serving. </p><br/><p class="no-indent">*We used Springer Mountain Farms Chicken.</p></div>
